<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>CAB: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - CAB DOOR GLASS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="5">
        <title>CAB DOOR GLASS</title>
        <svcsubproc id="x1600708">
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove door hardware and trim, if so equipped. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16007s_20.xml" xrefid="x1600706">Hardware and Trim, Remove</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Temporarily place the window regulator handle (Item 11,
                    <hotlnk document="s16007s_20.xml" xrefid="f1600714">Figure 14</hotlnk>) on the regulator handle
                    shaft (Item 1,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600727">Figure 27</hotlnk>), and lower door window glass (Item 2,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600727">Figure 27</hotlnk>) to the bottom of its channel.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1600727" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1600727" filename="../figg16/G1600727.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 27. Regulator Handle Shaft</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. REGULATOR HANDLE SHAFT</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. DOOR WINDOW GLASS</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. ACCESS OPENING</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600728">Figure 28</hotlnk>for Items in parentheses unless otherwise noted.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600728" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600728" filename="../figg16/G1600728.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 28. Window Regulator Lever</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WINDOW REGULATOR LEVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. WINDOW GLASS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WINDOW GUIDE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. DOOR ACCESS OPENING</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. FASTENER SCREWS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Working through the door access opening (Item 3,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600727">Figure 27</hotlnk>), remove two glass fastener screws (Item 5) from the
                    window guide (Item 3) and remove guide from window glass (Item 2) and window regulator lever roller
                    (Item 1). Run regulator lever up out of the way and remove regulator handle.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove access plug from side of door for access to rear run channel (Item 1,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600729">Figure 29</hotlnk>) upper retaining bolt. Remove bolt.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1600729" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1600729" filename="../figg16/G1600729.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 29. Rear Run Channel</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. REAR RUN CHANNEL</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. CHANNEL SEAL</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two retaining bolts from lower end of rear run channel (Item 1,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600729">Figure 29</hotlnk>) Remove channel and channel seal (Items 1 and 2,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600729">Figure 29</hotlnk>) from glass and lay aside in door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove glass from front run channel glass seal (Item 18,
                    <hotlnk document="s16007s_20.xml" xrefid="f1600715">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull glass out through access opening (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600730">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1600730" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1600730" filename="../figg16/G1600730.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 30. Access Opening</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. DOOR WINDOW GLASS</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. ACCESS OPENING</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x1600709">
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert window glass (Item 1,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600730">Figure 30</hotlnk>) through access opening (Item 2,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600730">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position glass into front run channel glass seal (Item 18,
                    <hotlnk document="s16007s_20.xml" xrefid="f1600715">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide rear run channel and channel seal (Items 1 and 2,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600729">Figure 29</hotlnk>) onto rear edge of glass.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure rear run channel upper and lower mounting brackets with bolts and washers.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When assured that glass will slide easily from top to bottom in window channel seals,
                    move window to lowered position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Temporarily install regulator handle (Item 11,
                    <hotlnk document="s16007s_20.xml" xrefid="f1600714">Figure 14</hotlnk>) and to engage with bottom
                    edge of window.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install window guide (Item 3,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600728">Figure 28</hotlnk>) and move regulator lever bottom edge of window.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install window guide (Item 3,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600728">Figure 28</hotlnk>) and regulator lever stud to window glass using the two
                    fastener screws (Item 5,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600728">Figure 28</hotlnk>) through holes provided in glass. Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600731">Figure 31</hotlnk>for fastener screw assembly.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1600731" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1600731" filename="../figg16/G1600731.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 31. Fastener Screw Assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. LOWER HALF FASTENER</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. UPPER HALF FASTENER</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. WINDOW GUIDE</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. SCREW</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. WINDOW GLASS</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Operate regulator handle to make sure all components have been assembled correctly.
                    Remove regulator handle.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install manifest pocket/cover panel or trim panel, if so equipped. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16007s_20.xml" xrefid="x1600707">Hardware and Trim, Install</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
